With its prism-like façade this new 24-story glass apartment tower reflects the increasing trend of luxury high-rise living in the South Loop. Located in the McCormick Square micro-neighborhood, renters of the 275 units here are near the sprawling McCormick Place Convention Center, Illinois Institute of Technology, and DePaul University’s Wintrust Arena.  Zip to the Loop in 10 minutes from the CTA Green Line Cermak-McCormick Place station just 1 block away. Drivers also have convenient access to Lake Shore Drive, I-55 and I-90 expressways.    There’s plenty to do around the neighborhood along Cermak Road, as well as adjacent Motor Row, Chinatown, Pilsen and Bronzeville with a growing surge of restaurants, brewery pubs, and entertainment venues. Culture and recreation are also nearby at the Museum Campus, Soldier Field, Northerly Island and the Lakefront Trail.  Live a lush life for less with amenities that rival other downtown high-end apartments, but at a more attainable price point compared to other Loop-adjacent neighborhoods such as West Loop, River North and Streeterville. Residents here can enjoy 25,000 square feet of amenity space including a fully-equipped fitness center, yoga studio with virtual trainer, private work spaces, conference room, club lounge with pub room, game/arcade room, sports simulator room, outdoor pool deck with fire pits, grilling stations and private cabanas. Convenient on-site services are also available including dry cleaning lockers, package receiving room, a guest suite, and bike storage.  Inside these apartments the warm earth tones welcome you to a soothing home environment. The uniquely styled kitchen finishes feature a mix of hues with European two-tone white and beige cabinetry, marbled light quartz countertops, gray tile backsplash and stainless steel appliances. Elements of on-trend exposed concrete ceilings and wide plank wood flooring also create a modern loft look. The floor-to-ceiling windows provide brilliant unobstructed views in all directions. Each unit also includes full-size washers and dryers, premium roller shades and keyless entry.   A private parking garage is available on-site for an additional monthly fee. Cats and dogs are welcome (dog breed and weight restrictions apply), and there is an on-site outdoor dog run for your fuzzy buddy too! Located on the south end of this super popular neighborhood, these rentals are also near the University of Illinois Chicago campus, Illinois Medical District hospitals and businesses in Chicago’s downtown Loop.    These smartly designed modern apartments feature luxury finishes including double pane floor-to-ceiling windows, 9’-12’ tall ceilings, modern kitchens and bathrooms, five-burner gas range, dishwasher, spacious custom-built closets, wide plank wood flooring, and washers and dryers. Plenty of shopping and dining options are just a short walks away, including Randolph Street “restaurant row,” Greektown on Halsted, and Little Italy and Pilsen are not too far away.  Dogs and cats are allowed, and pet parents will love that there are several large parks nearby including Skinner Park and Mary Bartelme Park. There’s also an on-site indoor/outdoor dog run and spa.   For everyday essentials, there’s a Target store 1 block away.  Whole Foods and Mariano’s grocery stores are also nearby, within a short walk. Getting around is a breeze, with the CTA Blue Line Racine station 1 block west, plus the Green and Pink Lines are about 10 minutes north at the Morgan station. Drivers have quick access to expressway, less than a minute to I-290 and about two minutes to I-90/94. These studio and 1 bedroom remodeled apartments for rent include in-unit washer & dryer, generously sized closets, jaw dropping views of the Chicago skyline and dishwashers in every kitchen. Chestnut Apartments you can walk to everything in the Gold Coast, River North, Streeterville, and a little further over the Chicago River you can be in the Chicago Loop. title: Walk to UIC,RUSH,VA,STROGER Med. Dist./HUGE, quiet, clean,charming -...
posting_body: QR Code Link to This Post   1200 sq. ft.! Available June 13th or a bit sooner. HUGE! Unique, quiet, clean, charming 1 bedroom w/separate office/storage room. Walk to Rush, UIC, Stroger and VA hospitals in the Medical District / Tri-Taylor area. Mansion like ceiling fixtures and bookcase woodwork detail around windows. Stained glass in dining room/Santa Fe style.  High ceilings. Original hardwood floors and ornate detail. Tenants have taken our suggestion and used the living room as a master suite as pictured in picture 5, then used dining room as living/dining room. The 1st, 2nd, 3rd and 4th pictures show the living room as such and dining room as such.  The place is that big and versatile. Nevertheless the master bedroom is double size and can fit any bed with furniture. There is an additional, separate 2nd room that is suited for multiuse/storage/office space not pictured. High ceilings lots of natural light if desired. Huge walk in closet in entrance hall. Kitchen has lots of cabinets and counter top space with walk in pantry. 1 bath w/ shower bath tub combo. Quiet outside private space with sitting porch. These are not loud party buildings where buddies can crash after a night of drinkin'.   We commit to providing a quiet and private space for our tenants who are mostly serious medical etc. students/residents. Usually convenient parking right in front, as neighbors have garages. Huge walk in closet in vestibule. Central heating and window AC'S. $1200 for 1 to 2 people. Please CALL 805-293-4218. NO TEXTS PLEASE...Thank you. No dogs, smoking, no drama. 1 declawed cat only after a former tenants cat scratched up historical, original woodwork. Ugh! Laundry on premises. Footsteps from public transportation, UIC shuttle. Lots of restaurants and small mini mart in neighborhood. On treelined streets in a lovely residential neighborhood. Apartment has private entrance. Only responsible landlord and tenants will have keys. Will be available June 1st. or a bit sooner. Flexible lease within reason available. 1st month's rent in advance and 1 month's security deposit.  Again NO texts please.  Rep will wear mask and social distance and require the same of anyone entering the building. No move in or applications fees. As about our other listings in the area under $1325.00 all walking distance to Medical District/West Campus.
